            "size": 1410,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_016RfEvU11bqfyWbr82hPF49\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Got it. Now let's talk about **how your solution actually works** for your users.\\n\\nSpecifically: What's the concrete process or mechanism that solves the host's pain point? Walk me through what happens when a host uses Friend of the Pod.\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Let's dig into how Friend of the Pod actually solves the problem. When a host signs up, what's the step-by-step process they go through to find their ideal guest? What does the experience look like?\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\n    \\\"Host fills out a brief profile → AI matches them with 10 vetted guests → Host books in one click\\\",\\n    \\\"Host describes their episode topic → System searches our guest database → Presents ranked matches with clips and bios\\\",\\n    \\\"Host inputs their niche and guest preferences → Algorithm filters thousands of candidates → Host gets a curated list ready to pitch\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Give me the flow—what does a host actually DO to get results?\\\"\\n}\\n```\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2429,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":236,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
