            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01JmU6JzAKd3UJoviPwVWtoe\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Perfect. Now let's talk about **social proof** for your landing page.\\n\\nThis is about building credibility and trust. Social proof can be testimonials from happy hosts or guests, but it can also be your founder story, your background, relevant experience, or even your beliefs about podcasting.\\n\\nWhat social proof or credibility can we highlight? For example: Have you worked in podcasting before? Do you have early users or beta testers? Any relevant experience or credentials?\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"What social proof or credibility should we highlight on your landing page? This could be testimonials from early users, your founder background, podcasting industry experience, or anything that builds trust.\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\n    \\\"Founder spent 5 years as a podcast producer and knows the pain firsthand\\\",\\n    \\\"Already have 50+ hosts using the platform with 4.8-star reviews\\\",\\n    \\\"Featured in Podcast Magazine or quoted by industry leaders\\\",\\n    \\\"Personal story: 'I spent 20 hours finding one guest—built this to never do that again'\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"What credibility or proof points can we use to make visitors trust Friend of the Pod?\\\"\\n}\\n```\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2652,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":278,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
