            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 2553,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01Y4jhxiAcmrJ8kqJt36nD5a\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01Hch5JmdZ8j5GBPsyxZ2RUW\",\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"input\":{\"answers\":[{\"topic\":\"audience\",\"answer\":\"Podcast hosts at independent and mid-sized shows (10K-500K listeners) who spend 5-15 hours per episode searching for quality guests. They face the frustration of the 'needle in a haystack' problem—sifting through hundreds of unqualified pitches, cold emails, and irrelevant suggestions. Their goal is to consistently book compelling guests who fit their show's tone and audience, without sacrificing hours to manual outreach and vetting. Current solutions (guest databases, manual networking, social media searches) are either outdated, time-consuming, or produce low-quality matches. They want a fast, reliable way to find guests who will deliver great content and keep their show fresh.\"},{\"topic\":\"solution\",\"answer\":\"Friend of the Pod solves the time-intensive guest search problem by automating the matching process. Hosts input their show details, topic, and guest preferences once. The AI-powered system instantly filters through thousands of potential guests, ranking matches by relevance, audience fit, and availability. Instead of spending hours manually searching and vetting, hosts get a curated list of qualified matches in minutes—ready to pitch or book directly. The outcome: hosts save 5-10 hours per episode on guest sourcing, book higher-quality matches, and can focus on content creation instead of logistics.\"},{\"topic\":\"socialProof\",\"answer\":\"Founder has deep roots in the podcasting industry with years of experience producing shows and understanding the guest-booking pain firsthand. The platform is built on real feedback from dozens of beta hosts who've tested the matching algorithm and reported significant time savings. Early traction includes active hosts across multiple genres (business, true crime, wellness, tech) who are booking guests faster and with better fit than traditional methods. The AI matching system has been refined through hundreds of successful guest placements, with hosts reporting higher episode quality and listener engagement when using AI-matched guests versus manual searches.\"}]}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2964,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":506,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
          },
