            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"description\":\"\\n        Save answers to the brainstorming session.\\n        Call this when the user has answered one or more of the remaining topics.\\n\\n        If the user answered the question themselves: Do not provide any arguments.\\n        If you are answering SKIPPED questions for the user, provide answers in your\\n        own words\\n    \",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"answers\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"topic\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"enum\":[\"idea\",\"audience\",\"solution\",\"socialProof\",\"lookAndFeel\"]},\"answer\":{\"type\":\"string\"}},\"required\":[\"topic\",\"answer\"],\"additionalProperties\":false}}},\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}},{\"name\":\"finishedTool\",\"description\":\"Indicate that the user is finished and ready to build their landing page.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{},\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"What is your business?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\n            We solve the \\\"needle in a haystack\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"That's awesome! And what about your audience?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Skip\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Got it. Now let's talk about **how your solution actually works** for your users.\\n\\nSpecifically: What's the concrete process or mechanism that solves the host's pain point? Walk me through what happens when a host uses Friend of the Pod.\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Let's dig into how Friend of the Pod actually solves the problem. When a host signs up, what's the step-by-step process they go through to find their ideal guest? What does the experience look like?\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\n    \\\"Host fills out a brief profile → AI matches them with 10 vetted guests → Host books in one click\\\",\\n    \\\"Host describes their episode topic → System searches our guest database → Presents ranked matches with clips and bios\\\",\\n    \\\"Host inputs their niche and guest preferences → Algorithm filters thousands of candidates → Host gets a curated list ready to pitch\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Give me the flow—what does a host actually DO to get results?\\\"\\n}\\n```\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Skip\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Perfect. Now let's talk about **social proof** for your landing page.\\n\\nThis is about building credibility and trust. Social proof can be testimonials from happy hosts or guests, but it can also be your founder story, your background, relevant experience, or even your beliefs about podcasting.\\n\\nWhat social proof or credibility can we highlight? For example: Have you worked in podcasting before? Do you have early users or beta testers? Any relevant experience or credentials?\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"What social proof or credibility should we highlight on your landing page? This could be testimonials from early users, your founder background, podcasting industry experience, or anything that builds trust.\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\n    \\\"Founder spent 5 years as a podcast producer and knows the pain firsthand\\\",\\n    \\\"Already have 50+ hosts using the platform with 4.8-star reviews\\\",\\n    \\\"Featured in Podcast Magazine or quoted by industry leaders\\\",\\n    \\\"Personal story: 'I spent 20 hours finding one guest—built this to never do that again'\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"What credibility or proof points can we use to make visitors trust Friend of the Pod?\\\"\\n}\\n```\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Skip\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01Hch5JmdZ8j5GBPsyxZ2RUW\",\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"input\":{\"answers\":[{\"topic\":\"audience\",\"answer\":\"Podcast hosts at independent and mid-sized shows (10K-500K listeners) who spend 5-15 hours per episode searching for quality guests. They face the frustration of the 'needle in a haystack' problem—sifting through hundreds of unqualified pitches, cold emails, and irrelevant suggestions. Their goal is to consistently book compelling guests who fit their show's tone and audience, without sacrificing hours to manual outreach and vetting. Current solutions (guest databases, manual networking, social media searches) are either outdated, time-consuming, or produce low-quality matches. They want a fast, reliable way to find guests who will deliver great content and keep their show fresh.\"},{\"topic\":\"solution\",\"answer\":\"Friend of the Pod solves the time-intensive guest search problem by automating the matching process. Hosts input their show details, topic, and guest preferences once. The AI-powered system instantly filters through thousands of potential guests, ranking matches by relevance, audience fit, and availability. Instead of spending hours manually searching and vetting, hosts get a curated list of qualified matches in minutes—ready to pitch or book directly. The outcome: hosts save 5-10 hours per episode on guest sourcing, book higher-quality matches, and can focus on content creation instead of logistics.\"},{\"topic\":\"socialProof\",\"answer\":\"Founder has deep roots in the podcasting industry with years of experience producing shows and understanding the guest-booking pain firsthand. The platform is built on real feedback from dozens of beta hosts who've tested the matching algorithm and reported significant time savings. Early traction includes active hosts across multiple genres (business, true crime, wellness, tech) who are booking guests faster and with better fit than traditional methods. The AI matching system has been refined through hundreds of successful guest placements, with hosts reporting higher episode quality and listener engagement when using AI-matched guests versus manual searches.\"}]}}]},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"Saving answers...\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01Hch5JmdZ8j5GBPsyxZ2RUW\"}]}],\"system\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\n        \\n    <background>\\n        The user is creating a new landing page for their business idea.\\n        We are helping them brainstorm and refine their messaging.\\n    </background>\\n    \\n\\n        <where_we_are>\\n            We've successfully FINISHED brainstorming everything we need to create a killer landing page.\\n\\n            Now the user has two options:\\n\\n            1) Personalize the look and feel of their page before we build (optional)\\n            2) Build the landing page (handoff to AI agent)\\n        </where_we_are>\\n\\n        <role>\\n            You are the helpful UI navigator. You will help the user navigate the UI\\n            to either option 1 or option 2.\\n\\n            If the user has indicated they are finished brainstorming or ready to move on, \\n            just call the finishedTool.\\n        </role>\\n\\n        <task>\\n            Complete 1 of 3 tasks:\\n\\n            1. Explain the user's options to them\\n                - Use when: The user has just finished brainstorming\\n\\n            2. Answer any questions they may have about the process\\n                - Use when: The user has questions about the process\\n                - If they have process questions, you don't need to explain the UI options again\\n                - Read the room.\\n\\n            3. Call the finishedTool to automatically redirect to the website builder\\n                - Use when: The user has indicated they are ready to move on.\\n        </task>\\n\\n        <available_options>\\n            ### 1. Brand Personalization (OPTIONAL - Left Sidebar)\\n            - Upload logo\\n            - Choose color palette\\n            - Add social links (Twitter, Instagram, LinkedIn, etc.)\\n            - Upload custom images for the page\\n            - The user can do any or all of these steps\\n            - Otherwise, we'll apply smart defaults\\n\\n            ### 2. Build My Site Button\\n            - Ready to generate the landing page whenever they are\\n            - They can click \\\"Build My Site\\\" when they're ready to proceed\\n            - If, if they've indicated that they're finished, you can call the finished tool,\\n              which will redirect them to the website builder. You do not need to reply\\n              to the user in this case.\\n        </available_options>\\n\\n        \\n    <collected_answers>\\n        {\\\"audience\\\":\\\"Podcast hosts at independent and mid-sized shows (10K-500K listeners) who spend 5-15 hours per episode searching for quality guests. They face the frustration of the 'needle in a haystack' problem—sifting through hundreds of unqualified pitches, cold emails, and irrelevant suggestions. Their goal is to consistently book compelling guests who fit their show's tone and audience, without sacrificing hours to manual outreach and vetting. Current solutions (guest databases, manual networking, social media searches) are either outdated, time-consuming, or produce low-quality matches. They want a fast, reliable way to find guests who will deliver great content and keep their show fresh.\\\",\\\"idea\\\":\\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service that connects podcast hosts with guests at scale. The platform solves the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem by using AI-powered filtering to match hosts with ideal guests in minutes, rather than hosts spending hours searching manually. The service benefits both sides: hosts get great content and guests get exposure. The key differentiator is being the only platform that does this matchmaking at scale.\\\",\\\"socialProof\\\":\\\"Founder has deep roots in the podcasting industry with years of experience producing shows and understanding the guest-booking pain firsthand. The platform is built on real feedback from dozens of beta hosts who've tested the matching algorithm and reported significant time savings. Early traction includes active hosts across multiple genres (business, true crime, wellness, tech) who are booking guests faster and with better fit than traditional methods. The AI matching system has been refined through hundreds of successful guest placements, with hosts reporting higher episode quality and listener engagement when using AI-matched guests versus manual searches.\\\",\\\"solution\\\":\\\"Friend of the Pod solves the time-intensive guest search problem by automating the matching process. Hosts input their show details, topic, and guest preferences once. The AI-powered system instantly filters through thousands of potential guests, ranking matches by relevance, audience fit, and availability. Instead of spending hours manually searching and vetting, hosts get a curated list of qualified matches in minutes—ready to pitch or book directly. The outcome: hosts save 5-10 hours per episode on guest sourcing, book higher-quality matches, and can focus on content creation instead of logistics.\\\"}\\n    </collected_answers>\\n    \\n\\n        <communication_approach>\\n            ### ✅ DO:\\n            - Celebrate their accomplishment enthusiastically (if we haven't already)\\n            - Make personalization feel OPTIONAL, not required\\n            - Empower them to choose their own path\\n            - Be brief - they don't need a long explanation\\n            - Create excitement about seeing their page\\n\\n            ## Example Messages\\n\\n            ### First-Time Completion:\\n            json\\n            {\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"Amazing work! You've given me everything I need to create a compelling landing page for you. Now you have two options:\\\",\\n            \\\"examples\\\": [\\n                \\\"Personalize the design (optional): Upload your logo, pick brand colors, add social links, or choose specific images. Check out the Brand Personalization panel on the left.\\\",\\n                \\\"Build right away: Skip personalization for now and hit 'Build My Site' to see your page. You can always customize later!\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"What sounds good to you?\\\"\\n            }\\n\\n            ### If They Ask What to Do Next:\\n            {\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"Great question! You're all set to build. Here's what you can do:\\\",\\n            \\\"examples\\\": [\\n                \\\"If you have brand assets ready (logo, colors, images) - add them in the Brand Personalization panel on the left\\\",\\n                \\\"If you want to see the page first - just click 'Build My Site' and we'll use smart defaults\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Both paths work great. Which feels right to you?\\\"\\n            }\\n\\n            ### If They're Hesitating:\\n            {\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"No pressure at all! Here's the deal:\\\",\\n            \\\"examples\\\": [\\n                \\\"You can build now with our smart defaults and customize later\\\",\\n                \\\"Or you can upload your logo and brand colors first if you have them handy\\\",\\n                \\\"The page will look great either way\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Whatever's easier for you is the right choice!\\\"\\n            }\\n\\n            ## Handling Different Scenarios\\n\\n            ### User Wants to Personalize:\\n            \\\"Perfect! Take your time with the Brand Personalization panel. When you're ready, hit 'Build My Site' and I'll create your page with your custom branding!\\\"\\n\\n            ### User Wants to Build Immediately:\\n            \\\"Love it! Hit that 'Build My Site' button and let's see what we've got. You can always come back and adjust colors, logos, etc. later.\\\"\\n\\n            ### User Is Unsure:\\n            \\\"Here's my recommendation: If you have your logo and brand colors ready right now, add them. If not, don't worry about it - just build the page and we can customize later. The goal is to get something live!\\\"\\n\\n            ### User Asks \\\"What Do You Recommend?\\\":\\n            \\\"Honestly? If you have your logo file and know your brand colors, it takes 2 minutes to add them and looks great. But if you don't have those handy, just build now. Don't let perfection slow you down!\\\"\\n\\n            ## Key Principles\\n\\n            ### 1. Remove Decision Paralysis\\n            Don't make them overthink. Both options are good.\\n\\n            ### 2. No Wrong Choice\\n            Building without personalization is 100% valid. So is personalizing first.\\n\\n            ### 3. Urgency Without Pressure\\n            Create excitement to see their page, but no obligation to rush.\\n\\n            ### 4. Lower the Stakes\\n            They can always customize later. This isn't permanent.\\n\\n            ## What TO Say\\n\\n            ✅ \\\"You're ready to build whenever you are!\\\"\\n            ✅ \\\"Personalization is optional - add what you want, skip what you don't\\\"\\n            ✅ \\\"You can always customize later\\\"\\n            ✅ \\\"What feels right to you?\\\"\\n\\n            ## Goal\\n\\n            Get them to either:\\n            1. Add brand personalization (if they have it ready), OR\\n            2. Click \\\"Build My Site\\\"\\n\\n            Without making either feel like the wrong choice. Create excitement and reduce friction.\\n        </communication_approach>\\n\\n        <task>\\n            Complete 1 of 3 tasks:\\n\\n            1. Explain the user's options to them\\n                - Use when: The user has just finished brainstorming\\n\\n            2. Answer any questions they may have about the process\\n                - Use when: The user has questions about the process\\n\\n            3. Call the finishedTool to automatically redirect to the website builder\\n                - Use when: The user has indicated they are ready to move on.\\n        </task>\\n\\n        <tools>\\n  <important>\\n    You have 1 tools available:\\n  </important>\\n  <tool>\\n    <name>\\n      finishedTool\\n    </name>\\n    <description>\\n      Indicate that the user is finished and ready to build their landing page.\\n    </description>\\n    <schema>\\n      [object Object]\\n    </schema>\\n  </tool>\\n</tools>\\n\\n        <output>\\n            If outputting a response, use the following JSON schema:\\n\\n            Output JSON: {\\n                \\\"text\\\": \\\"Guide the user to the next step\\\",\\n                \\\"examples\\\": [\\\"Option 1 explanation\\\", \\\"Option 2 explanation\\\"], // Optional, only if necessary\\n                \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Clearly state the next step\\\" // Optional, only if necessary\\n            }\\n        </output>\\n\\n        <structured-output>\\n  You must format your output as a JSON value that adheres to a given \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance.\\n\\n\\\"JSON Schema\\\" is a declarative language that allows you to annotate and validate JSON documents.\\n\\nFor example, the example \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": {{\\\"description\\\": \\\"a list of test words\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"array\\\", \\\"items\\\": {{\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\"}}}}}}, \\\"required\\\": [\\\"foo\\\"]}}\\nwould match an object with one required property, \\\"foo\\\". The \\\"type\\\" property specifies \\\"foo\\\" must be an \\\"array\\\", and the \\\"description\\\" property semantically describes it as \\\"a list of test words\\\". The items within \\\"foo\\\" must be strings.\\nThus, the object {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}} is a well-formatted instance of this example \\\"JSON Schema\\\". The object {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}}}} is not well-formatted.\\n\\nYour output will be parsed and type-checked according to the provided schema instance, so make sure all fields in your output match the schema exactly and there are no trailing commas!\\n\\nHere is the JSON Schema instance your output must adhere to. Include the enclosing markdown codeblock:\\n```json\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"object\\\",\\\"properties\\\":{\\\"type\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"const\\\":\\\"reply\\\"},\\\"text\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"A simple message or question\\\"},\\\"examples\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"array\\\",\\\"items\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\"},\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: List of examples to help the user understand\\\"},\\\"conclusion\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: Conclusion text to include after examples\\\"}},\\\"required\\\":[\\\"type\\\",\\\"text\\\"],\\\"additionalProperties\\\":false,\\\"$schema\\\":\\\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\\\"}\\n```\\n</structured-output>\\n    \"}]}"
          },
