            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 2331,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01D4TMpWBTEW731o9NNsZTR5\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"helpMe\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Perfect! Let me help you get specific about who you're selling to and what keeps them up at night.\\\",\\n  \\\"template\\\": \\\"**1. Who are they?**\\\\n[Job title/role] at [company size/type] who [specific context about their work]\\\\n\\\\n**2. What's their main problem?**\\\\nThey spend [time/effort] trying to [specific task], which results in [frustration or consequence]\\\\n\\\\n**3. What are they actually trying to achieve?**\\\\nThey want to [desired outcome] so they can [bigger goal or benefit]\\\\n\\\\n**4. Why haven't they solved this yet?**\\\\nExisting solutions [describe what's broken about current options]\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\n    \\\"**1. Who:** Podcast hosts at mid-sized media companies (50-500 employees) who produce 1-3 shows per week\\\\n\\\\n**2. Problem:** They spend 5-10 hours per week manually searching LinkedIn, Twitter, and email lists trying to find guests who fit their niche, and they often end up with mediocre interviews because they're running out of time\\\\n\\\\n**3. Goal:** They want to fill their guest slots with relevant, credible people consistently so their show stays engaging and their audience keeps growing\\\\n\\\\n**4. Why it's broken:** Guest databases are outdated, cold outreach has low response rates, and hiring a producer to find guests costs $3-5K/month\\\",\\n    \\\"**1. Who:** Solo podcast creators or small teams (1-3 people) running niche shows in B2B spaces like SaaS, marketing, or finance\\\\n\\\\n**2. Problem:** They manually vet hundreds of potential guests, waste time on no-shows, and struggle to find people with actual expertise in their specific topic\\\\n\\\\n**3. Goal:** They want a reliable stream of interesting guests so they can focus on recording and growing their audience instead of sourcing\\\\n\\\\n**4. Why it's broken:** Generic guest networks don't understand their niche, and personal networking only gets you so far\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3051,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":498,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
