            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"description\":\"\\n        Save answers to the brainstorming session.\\n        Call this when the user has answered one or more of the remaining topics.\\n\\n        If the user answered the question themselves: Do not provide any arguments.\\n        If you are answering SKIPPED questions for the user, provide answers in your\\n        own words\\n    \",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"answers\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"topic\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"enum\":[\"idea\",\"audience\",\"solution\",\"socialProof\",\"lookAndFeel\"]},\"answer\":{\"type\":\"string\"}},\"required\":[\"topic\",\"answer\"],\"additionalProperties\":false}}},\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}},{\"name\":\"finishedTool\",\"description\":\"Indicate that the user is finished and ready to build their landing page.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{},\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}},{\"name\":\"query_uploads\",\"description\":\"Query the user's uploaded images for this project.\\nUse this tool when the user mentions images they've uploaded previously but aren't\\nattached to the current message. For example:\\n- \\\"Use the product photos I uploaded earlier\\\"\\n- \\\"Can you see my recent image uploads?\\\"\\n- \\\"Use the logo I uploaded\\\"\\n\\nReturns a list of uploaded images with their URLs and metadata.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"query_type\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"enum\":[\"recent\",\"logos\",\"all\"],\"description\":\"Type of images to query: 'recent' for most recent product images, 'logos' for logo images only, 'all' for all images\"},\"limit\":{\"type\":\"number\",\"description\":\"Maximum number of images to return. Defaults to 10.\"}},\"required\":[\"query_type\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"What is your business?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\n            We solve the \\\"needle in a haystack\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"That's awesome! And what about your audience?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Please do the rest for me\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I'll create plausible answers for the three skipped topics based on the strong foundation you've provided about Friend of the Pod.\"},{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01JLJheLYa8vmA3dKDNZhUGK\",\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"input\":{\"answers\":[{\"topic\":\"audience\",\"answer\":\"**Who are they?** Podcast hosts running shows with 5K-500K listeners who are actively producing content weekly or bi-weekly. They're typically entrepreneurs, thought leaders, or media professionals aged 28-55 who take their show seriously but don't have a dedicated production team.\\n\\n**What problems do they face?** Finding quality guests is incredibly time-consuming and frustrating. Hosts spend 3-5 hours per week manually searching LinkedIn, Twitter, and email lists, often ending up with mediocre guests or no-shows. They feel the pressure to maintain consistent, high-quality content but lack a systematic way to source interesting people. Many resort to asking the same guests repeatedly, leading to stale content.\\n\\n**What are they trying to achieve?** They want to produce compelling episodes that attract and retain listeners, build their personal brand, and grow their audience. They're looking for a way to consistently book credible, interesting guests without the exhausting manual search process.\\n\\n**Why existing solutions fail:** Current options are fragmented—guest databases are outdated, cold outreach has low response rates, and guest networks are either too niche or too generic. There's no intelligent matching system that understands both what hosts need and what guests want.\"},{\"topic\":\"solution\",\"answer\":\"**What specific problem does it solve?** The hours hosts waste manually searching for guests—the \\\"needle in a haystack\\\" problem. Instead of spending 3-5 hours per week sifting through LinkedIn, email lists, and networks, hosts face the friction of finding people who are both credible AND willing to appear.\\n\\n**How does it work?** Friend of the Pod uses AI-powered filtering to understand what makes a great guest match for each specific show. The platform analyzes host preferences, audience demographics, and content themes, then intelligently matches them with ideal guests from a large database in minutes. The matching works both ways—guests also get matched with shows that align with their expertise and goals.\\n\\n**What outcome do customers get?** Hosts can book quality guests in minutes instead of hours, maintain consistent episode schedules without the stress of last-minute scrambling, and ultimately produce better content that keeps listeners engaged. Guests get exposure to relevant audiences without having to pitch themselves everywhere. Both sides win.\"},{\"topic\":\"socialProof\",\"answer\":\"**Your credentials and founder story:** [Founder background—e.g., \\\"As a podcast producer for 6+ years, I personally experienced the pain of finding guests and watched dozens of hosts struggle with the same problem. I built Friend of the Pod to solve what I knew was broken.\\\"]\\n\\n**Traction signals:** Early adopters and beta users who've experienced the time savings and quality of matches. [Include: number of hosts using platform, number of successful matches made, or growth metrics if available.]\\n\\n**Customer results/metrics:** Hosts booking guests in minutes instead of hours; reduced time spent on guest sourcing; improved episode consistency and listener retention. [Include specific examples: \\\"One host reduced guest-sourcing time from 4 hours/week to 15 minutes/week\\\" or similar.]\\n\\n**Recognition and partnerships:** Any podcast networks, platforms, or industry figures who've endorsed or partnered with Friend of the Pod. Media mentions or features in podcast industry publications.\\n\\n**The problem you're solving:** The fact that you identified and are solving a real, widespread pain point that no other platform addresses at scale is itself credibility—you're the only one doing this.\"}]}}]},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"Saving answers...\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01JLJheLYa8vmA3dKDNZhUGK\"}]}],\"system\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\n        \\n    <background>\\n        The user is creating a new landing page for their business idea.\\n        We are helping them brainstorm and refine their messaging.\\n    </background>\\n    \\n\\n        <where_we_are>\\n            We've successfully FINISHED brainstorming everything we need to create a killer landing page.\\n\\n            Now the user has two options:\\n\\n            1) Personalize the look and feel of their page before we build (optional)\\n            2) Build the landing page (handoff to AI agent)\\n        </where_we_are>\\n\\n        <role>\\n            You are the helpful UI navigator. You will help the user navigate the UI\\n            to either option 1 or option 2.\\n\\n            If the user has indicated they are finished brainstorming or ready to move on, \\n            just call the finishedTool.\\n        </role>\\n\\n        <task>\\n            Complete 1 of 3 tasks:\\n\\n            1. Explain the user's options to them\\n                - Use when: The user has just finished brainstorming\\n\\n            2. Answer any questions they may have about the process\\n                - Use when: The user has questions about the process\\n                - If they have process questions, you don't need to explain the UI options again\\n                - Read the room.\\n\\n            3. Call the finishedTool to automatically redirect to the website builder\\n                - Use when: The user has indicated they are ready to move on.\\n        </task>\\n\\n        <available_options>\\n            ### 1. Brand Personalization (OPTIONAL - Left Sidebar)\\n            - Upload logo\\n            - Choose color palette\\n            - Add social links (Twitter, Instagram, LinkedIn, etc.)\\n            - Upload custom images for the page\\n            - The user can do any or all of these steps\\n            - Otherwise, we'll apply smart defaults\\n\\n            ### 2. Build My Site Button\\n            - Ready to generate the landing page whenever they are\\n            - They can click \\\"Build My Site\\\" when they're ready to proceed\\n            - If, if they've indicated that they're finished, you can call the finished tool,\\n              which will redirect them to the website builder. You do not need to reply\\n              to the user in this case.\\n        </available_options>\\n\\n        \\n    <collected_answers>\\n        {\\\"audience\\\":\\\"**Who are they?** Podcast hosts running shows with 5K-500K listeners who are actively producing content weekly or bi-weekly. They're typically entrepreneurs, thought leaders, or media professionals aged 28-55 who take their show seriously but don't have a dedicated production team.\\\\n\\\\n**What problems do they face?** Finding quality guests is incredibly time-consuming and frustrating. Hosts spend 3-5 hours per week manually searching LinkedIn, Twitter, and email lists, often ending up with mediocre guests or no-shows. They feel the pressure to maintain consistent, high-quality content but lack a systematic way to source interesting people. Many resort to asking the same guests repeatedly, leading to stale content.\\\\n\\\\n**What are they trying to achieve?** They want to produce compelling episodes that attract and retain listeners, build their personal brand, and grow their audience. They're looking for a way to consistently book credible, interesting guests without the exhausting manual search process.\\\\n\\\\n**Why existing solutions fail:** Current options are fragmented—guest databases are outdated, cold outreach has low response rates, and guest networks are either too niche or too generic. There's no intelligent matching system that understands both what hosts need and what guests want.\\\",\\\"idea\\\":\\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service that connects podcast hosts with guests at scale. The platform solves the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem by using AI-powered filtering to match hosts with ideal guests in minutes, rather than hosts spending hours searching manually. The service benefits both sides: hosts get great content and guests get exposure. The key differentiator is being the only platform that does this matchmaking at scale.\\\",\\\"socialProof\\\":\\\"**Your credentials and founder story:** [Founder background—e.g., \\\\\\\"As a podcast producer for 6+ years, I personally experienced the pain of finding guests and watched dozens of hosts struggle with the same problem. I built Friend of the Pod to solve what I knew was broken.\\\\\\\"]\\\\n\\\\n**Traction signals:** Early adopters and beta users who've experienced the time savings and quality of matches. [Include: number of hosts using platform, number of successful matches made, or growth metrics if available.]\\\\n\\\\n**Customer results/metrics:** Hosts booking guests in minutes instead of hours; reduced time spent on guest sourcing; improved episode consistency and listener retention. [Include specific examples: \\\\\\\"One host reduced guest-sourcing time from 4 hours/week to 15 minutes/week\\\\\\\" or similar.]\\\\n\\\\n**Recognition and partnerships:** Any podcast networks, platforms, or industry figures who've endorsed or partnered with Friend of the Pod. Media mentions or features in podcast industry publications.\\\\n\\\\n**The problem you're solving:** The fact that you identified and are solving a real, widespread pain point that no other platform addresses at scale is itself credibility—you're the only one doing this.\\\",\\\"solution\\\":\\\"**What specific problem does it solve?** The hours hosts waste manually searching for guests—the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem. Instead of spending 3-5 hours per week sifting through LinkedIn, email lists, and networks, hosts face the friction of finding people who are both credible AND willing to appear.\\\\n\\\\n**How does it work?** Friend of the Pod uses AI-powered filtering to understand what makes a great guest match for each specific show. The platform analyzes host preferences, audience demographics, and content themes, then intelligently matches them with ideal guests from a large database in minutes. The matching works both ways—guests also get matched with shows that align with their expertise and goals.\\\\n\\\\n**What outcome do customers get?** Hosts can book quality guests in minutes instead of hours, maintain consistent episode schedules without the stress of last-minute scrambling, and ultimately produce better content that keeps listeners engaged. Guests get exposure to relevant audiences without having to pitch themselves everywhere. Both sides win.\\\"}\\n    </collected_answers>\\n    \\n\\n        <communication_approach>\\n            ### ✅ DO:\\n            - Celebrate their accomplishment enthusiastically (if we haven't already)\\n            - Make personalization feel OPTIONAL, not required\\n            - Empower them to choose their own path\\n            - Be brief - they don't need a long explanation\\n            - Create excitement about seeing their page\\n\\n            ## Example Messages\\n\\n            ### First-Time Completion:\\n            json\\n            {\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"Amazing work! You've given me everything I need to create a compelling landing page for you. Now you have two options:\\\",\\n            \\\"examples\\\": [\\n                \\\"Personalize the design (optional): Upload your logo, pick brand colors, add social links, or choose specific images. Check out the Brand Personalization panel on the left.\\\",\\n                \\\"Build right away: Skip personalization for now and hit 'Build My Site' to see your page. You can always customize later!\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"What sounds good to you?\\\"\\n            }\\n\\n            ### If They Ask What to Do Next:\\n            {\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"Great question! You're all set to build. Here's what you can do:\\\",\\n            \\\"examples\\\": [\\n                \\\"If you have brand assets ready (logo, colors, images) - add them in the Brand Personalization panel on the left\\\",\\n                \\\"If you want to see the page first - just click 'Build My Site' and we'll use smart defaults\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Both paths work great. Which feels right to you?\\\"\\n            }\\n\\n            ### If They're Hesitating:\\n            {\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"No pressure at all! Here's the deal:\\\",\\n            \\\"examples\\\": [\\n                \\\"You can build now with our smart defaults and customize later\\\",\\n                \\\"Or you can upload your logo and brand colors first if you have them handy\\\",\\n                \\\"The page will look great either way\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Whatever's easier for you is the right choice!\\\"\\n            }\\n\\n            ## Handling Different Scenarios\\n\\n            ### User Wants to Personalize:\\n            \\\"Perfect! Take your time with the Brand Personalization panel. When you're ready, hit 'Build My Site' and I'll create your page with your custom branding!\\\"\\n\\n            ### User Wants to Build Immediately:\\n            \\\"Love it! Hit that 'Build My Site' button and let's see what we've got. You can always come back and adjust colors, logos, etc. later.\\\"\\n\\n            ### User Is Unsure:\\n            \\\"Here's my recommendation: If you have your logo and brand colors ready right now, add them. If not, don't worry about it - just build the page and we can customize later. The goal is to get something live!\\\"\\n\\n            ### User Asks \\\"What Do You Recommend?\\\":\\n            \\\"Honestly? If you have your logo file and know your brand colors, it takes 2 minutes to add them and looks great. But if you don't have those handy, just build now. Don't let perfection slow you down!\\\"\\n\\n            ## Key Principles\\n\\n            ### 1. Remove Decision Paralysis\\n            Don't make them overthink. Both options are good.\\n\\n            ### 2. No Wrong Choice\\n            Building without personalization is 100% valid. So is personalizing first.\\n\\n            ### 3. Urgency Without Pressure\\n            Create excitement to see their page, but no obligation to rush.\\n\\n            ### 4. Lower the Stakes\\n            They can always customize later. This isn't permanent.\\n\\n            ## What TO Say\\n\\n            ✅ \\\"You're ready to build whenever you are!\\\"\\n            ✅ \\\"Personalization is optional - add what you want, skip what you don't\\\"\\n            ✅ \\\"You can always customize later\\\"\\n            ✅ \\\"What feels right to you?\\\"\\n\\n            ## Goal\\n\\n            Get them to either:\\n            1. Add brand personalization (if they have it ready), OR\\n            2. Click \\\"Build My Site\\\"\\n\\n            Without making either feel like the wrong choice. Create excitement and reduce friction.\\n        </communication_approach>\\n\\n        <task>\\n            Complete 1 of 4 tasks:\\n\\n            1. Explain the user's options to them\\n                - Use when: The user has just finished brainstorming\\n\\n            2. Answer any questions they may have about the process\\n                - Use when: The user has questions about the process\\n\\n            3. Call the finishedTool to automatically redirect to the website builder\\n                - Use when: The user has indicated they are ready to move on.\\n\\n            4. Query the user's uploaded images\\n                - Use when: The user mentions images they've uploaded previously\\n                - Call the query_uploads tool to fetch their images\\n        </task>\\n\\n        <tools>\\n  <important>\\n    You have 1 tools available:\\n  </important>\\n  <tool>\\n    <name>\\n      finishedTool\\n    </name>\\n    <description>\\n      Indicate that the user is finished and ready to build their landing page.\\n    </description>\\n    <schema>\\n      [object Object]\\n    </schema>\\n  </tool>\\n</tools>\\n\\n        <output>\\n            If outputting a response, use the following JSON schema:\\n\\n            Output JSON: {\\n                \\\"text\\\": \\\"Guide the user to the next step\\\",\\n                \\\"examples\\\": [\\\"Option 1 explanation\\\", \\\"Option 2 explanation\\\"], // Optional, only if necessary\\n                \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Clearly state the next step\\\" // Optional, only if necessary\\n            }\\n        </output>\\n\\n        <structured-output>\\n  You must format your output as a JSON value that adheres to a given \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance.\\n\\n\\\"JSON Schema\\\" is a declarative language that allows you to annotate and validate JSON documents.\\n\\nFor example, the example \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": {{\\\"description\\\": \\\"a list of test words\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"array\\\", \\\"items\\\": {{\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\"}}}}}}, \\\"required\\\": [\\\"foo\\\"]}}\\nwould match an object with one required property, \\\"foo\\\". The \\\"type\\\" property specifies \\\"foo\\\" must be an \\\"array\\\", and the \\\"description\\\" property semantically describes it as \\\"a list of test words\\\". The items within \\\"foo\\\" must be strings.\\nThus, the object {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}} is a well-formatted instance of this example \\\"JSON Schema\\\". The object {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}}}} is not well-formatted.\\n\\nYour output will be parsed and type-checked according to the provided schema instance, so make sure all fields in your output match the schema exactly and there are no trailing commas!\\n\\nHere is the JSON Schema instance your output must adhere to. Include the enclosing markdown codeblock:\\n```json\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"object\\\",\\\"properties\\\":{\\\"type\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"const\\\":\\\"reply\\\"},\\\"text\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"A simple message or question\\\"},\\\"examples\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"array\\\",\\\"items\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\"},\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: List of examples to help the user understand\\\"},\\\"conclusion\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: Conclusion text to include after examples\\\"}},\\\"required\\\":[\\\"type\\\",\\\"text\\\"],\\\"additionalProperties\\\":false,\\\"$schema\\\":\\\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\\\"}\\n```\\n</structured-output>\\n    \"}]}"
          },
          "queryString": [],
          "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages"
        },
        "response": {
          "bodySize": 1177,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1177,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_011YkCiTmxQQTpvCudhS3rfV\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Perfect! 🎉 I've filled in the remaining sections based on your core concept. Now you're all set with everything we need to build your landing page!\\n\\nHere's what you can do next:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Amazing work! You've given me everything I need to create a compelling landing page for Friend of the Pod. Now you have two options:\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\n    \\\"Personalize the design (optional): Upload your logo, pick brand colors, add social links, or choose specific images. Check out the Brand Personalization panel on the left.\\\",\\n    \\\"Build right away: Skip personalization for now and hit 'Build My Site' to see your page live. You can always customize later!\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"What sounds good to you?\\\"\\n}\\n```\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":5104,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":191,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
